newsitem.title: NETHERLANDS: USDA and dollar keep European feeds trade calm.
newsitem.headline: USDA and dollar keep European feeds trade calm.

text.p: Business on the European meals and feeds market remained quietly this afternoon as a stronger dollar and neutral to bearishly interprested USDA 97/98 soybean ending stocks kept buyers sidelined, market sources said.
The only trades reported were arrived Argentine soymeal pellets traded at $249 a tonne cif Amsterdam and August Dutch high protein soymeal at $287 a tonne fob Rotterdam.

"The dollar soared to 1.70 marks and USDA's 1997/98 soybean ending stocks at 285 million bushels from 240 million caused European operators to stay sidelined expecting a weaker Chicago opening, one broker said.--KAREL LUIMES +31 20 504 5832
